<paragraph id="8BFEAA64DC05FFA20DD6FCC2FDDE6E52" blockId="6.[140,1108,342,1671]" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DD6FCC2FF3E684F" bold="true" box="[185,251,800,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DD6FCC2FF30684F" box="[185,245,800,826]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" reason="1">Note</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species as well as 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20F60FCC3FDBF684F" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[527,634,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20F60FCC3FDE0684F" box="[527,549,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20F59FCC2FDBF684F" box="[566,634,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20FD5FCC3FC93684F" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[698,854,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consobrina">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20FD5FCC3FD15684F" box="[698,720,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20F8DFCC2FC93684F" box="[738,854,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">consobrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were all described by Guenée at the same time in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20F56FCA1FD506828" authorityName="Ochsenheimer. Hampson" authorityYear="1816" box="[569,661,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ophiusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20F56FCA1FD506828" box="[569,661,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Ophiusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and probably from specimens or paintings he received from Abbot via Smith. Th ey probably originated from eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F356EAF4DC05FFA20E95FC85FB9168F4" box="[1018,1108,871,897]" name="Georgia" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Georgia</collectingCountry>
or South Carolina in the vicinity of Savannah, where Abbot lived. Th e brief description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20DC4FC4CFED968B2" authorityName="Guenee in Boisduval and Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[171,284,941,968]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ophiusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DC4FC4CFF0468B2" box="[171,193,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DBFFC4FFED968B2" box="[208,284,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Guenée and accompanying painting could refer to one of two externally similar species, one of which is described as new below. Neither the description nor the painting of the species that served as a model for the description can be identified as to species. However, Abbot also painted the caterpillar and Guenée included a brief description of it as well. Most importantly, the food plant was identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20979FBD9FE846F02" authority="Aiton" authorityName="Aiton" authorityYear="1789" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20979FBD9FF3F6F02" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Fagus ferruginea</emphasis>
Aiton
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20CE5FBBCFD616F0D" authority="Ehrhart" authorityName="Ehrhart" box="[394,676,1117,1144]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandifolia">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20CE5FBBCFD816F02" box="[394,580,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Fagus grandifolia</emphasis>
Ehrhart
</taxonomicName>
) and the pupae was said to be covered with a thick effl orescence of white purple. A white, waxy bloom on the pupa is characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20C7AFB46FEBB6FC8" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[277,382,1187,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20C7AFB46FEEE6FC8" box="[277,299,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20C55FB41FEBB6FC8" box="[314,382,1187,1213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20F07FB46FC8A6FC8" authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[616,847,1187,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Argyrostrotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20F07FB46FD2B6FCB" box="[616,750,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Argyrostrotis</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20EE6FB41FECC6F94" authority="Schrank. Apparently" authorityName="Schrank. Apparently" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Catocala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20EE6FB41FC2D6FC8" box="[905,1000,1187,1213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Catocala</emphasis>
Schrank. Apparently
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20C7DFB25FE406F94" authorityName="Guenee in Boisduval and Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[274,389,1223,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ophiusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20C7DFB25FEED6F95" box="[274,296,1223,1248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20C56FB25FE406F94" box="[313,389,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been reared again but beech trees are characteristic of mesic forests in the coastal plain and do not occur in the swamp forests where the new species 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20D8FFAECFE856E52" authorityName="Sullivan. St. Tammany Parish" authorityYear="2010" box="[224,320,1293,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telma">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20D8FFAECFF336E52" box="[224,246,1294,1319]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20C6BFAEFFE856E52" box="[260,320,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">telma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35BF9EFDC05FFA30DD6FAD2FE5A6E08" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="92" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFEAA64DC05FFA20DD6FAD2FE7B6DF2" blockId="6.[140,1108,342,1671]" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DD6FAD2FEFD6E3F" bold="true" box="[185,312,1328,1354]" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DD6FAD2FEF66E3F" box="[185,307,1328,1354]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Adults of 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20CDDFAD3FDE66E3F" authorityName="Guenee in Boisduval and Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[434,547,1328,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ophiusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20CDDFAD3FE0D6E3F" box="[434,456,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20CB8FAD2FDE66E3F" box="[471,547,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20EE7FAD3FBE46E3F" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[904,1057,1328,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consobrina">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20EE7FAD3FC5B6E3F" box="[904,926,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20EC2FAD2FBE46E3F" box="[941,1057,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">consobrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20DE3FAB6FF336E18" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Guenee" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[140,246,1363,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DE3FAB6FF676E18" box="[140,162,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DDDFAB1FF336E18" box="[178,246,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the two triangular outward projections of the PM line. However, there is no reliable external character to distinguish it from the newly described species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20959FA95FF0D6EC1" authorityName="Sullivan. St. Tammany Parish" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telma">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20959FA95FB896EE5" box="[1078,1100,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DE3FA78FF0D6EC1" box="[140,200,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">telma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Upon dissection of the male genitalia 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20FEEFA79FD346EC1" authorityName="Guenee in Boisduval and Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[641,753,1434,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ophiusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20FEEFA79FD526EC1" box="[641,663,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20FCAFA78FD346EC1" box="[677,753,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a shorter and broader valva and the medial projection on the tegumen is more than half the length of the valva. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20DE3FA03FF296E8F" authorityName="Sullivan. St. Tammany Parish" authorityYear="2010" box="[140,236,1504,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telma">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DE3FA03FF676E8F" box="[140,162,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20DDFFA02FF296E8F" box="[176,236,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">telma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the valva is much narrower and longer and the medial projection of the tegumen is rarely as long as half the length of the valva. In females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20E36F9E6FC0D6D68" authorityName="Guenee in Boisduval and Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[857,968,1539,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ophiusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20E36F9E6FCAA6D68" box="[857,879,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20E13F9E1FC0D6D68" box="[892,968,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the distance between the lateral edges of the lodix and the main plate is less than the thickness of the lateral edge at its base. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC05FFA20CB4F9A9FDF96D11" authorityName="Sullivan. St. Tammany Parish" authorityYear="2010" box="[475,572,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telma">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20CB4F9A9FE346D11" box="[475,497,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9357676DC05FFA20F6FF9A8FDF96D11" box="[512,572,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">telma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this distance is much greater than the width of the base of the lateral edge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFEAA64DC04FFA30DE3FAE5FE5A6E08" blockId="7.[140,1108,1287,1405]" pageId="7" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="B9357676DC04FFA30DE3FAE5FEEE6E68" bold="true" box="[140,299,1287,1309]" pageId="7" pageNumber="92">Figures ΙΙ–Ι4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C41D1E7DC04FFA30C5FFAE5FE5A6E69" authorityName="Sullivan" authorityYear="2010" box="[304,415,1287,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Neadysgonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
